Class AsyncCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.SendableBase
      • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
        • org.team1540.rooster.util.AsyncCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sendable, AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleAsyncCommand
    public abstract class AsyncCommand
extends Command
    A Command that spawns off a new Notifier on initialization and stops it. That thread will call the runPeriodic() ()} method at a user-specified interval with precise timings.
    See Also:
    Thread

    • Method Detail

      • runPeriodic

        protected void runPeriodic()
        Runs the action of this command.

        This is equivalent to the Command.execute() method in normal commands. Note that this method will be called in a seperate thread, and as such any public methods it calls, fields it uses, etc. MUST be thread-safe.

      • runInitial

        protected void runInitial()
        Runs initialization code for this command. This is equivalent to the Command.initialize() method.

      • runEnd

        protected void runEnd()
        Called when the AsyncCommand ends peacefully. This is equivalent to Command.end(). This method is called when the command ends peacefully, i.e. when markAsFinished() was called. However, it is possible that another command interrupts this command after markAsFinished() was called but before the command was removed from the scheduler, and as such this method might not be called even if markAsFinished() was called.

      • runInterrupt

        protected void runInterrupt()
        Called when the AsyncCommand is interrupted. This method serves an identical purpose to Command.interrupted(). By default, this method calls runEnd().

      • markAsFinished

        protected void markAsFinished()
        Marks the command as finished. The runPeriodic() method will no longer be called, and the command will be canceled on the next scheduler tick.
